modules.description: This module implements statistical calculations, tuple manipulation, and file handling operations. It provides functions for computing standard deviation, enforcing conditions with custom error messages, restructuring tuples, and combining multiple lists into tuples. It also supports working with temporary files by creating, writing to, and passing file paths to a given function.

This module trains and evaluates Random Forest models for regression or classification tasks using the ranger C++ library. It operates on CSV files with headers, where one column is designated as the target variable. The trained model can predict values with optional standard deviation estimates, using either a single thread or parallel execution.

This module combines statistical analysis and machine learning capabilities, enabling data processing and model training workflows. It supports key operations like standard deviation calculation, tuple restructuring, CSV-based Random Forest training, and prediction with uncertainty estimation. Users can load data from files, train models with configurable parameters, and generate predictions while optionally leveraging parallel execution. Example tasks include analyzing numerical datasets, transforming tuple structures, and building regression or classification models from CSV input with header-parsed columns.
